      <!-- ================================================================ -->
      <!-- TEXT 2 — English translation                                     -->
      <!--                                                                  -->
      <!-- Each <seg corresp="#seg-N"> corresponds to <seg xml:id="seg-N"> -->
      <!-- in the Latin edition above. In TEI Publisher this can be         -->
      <!-- configured to render as a parallel column.                       -->
      <!-- ================================================================ -->
      <text xml:lang="en" type="translation">
        <body>
          <p>
            <seg corresp="#seg1"> <heading> Following the effects of the Body of
              Christ.</heading>
            </seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg2"> Just as Reymundus says:
              <quote>
                this sacrament of the Body of Christ accomplishes eternity
                and immortality for those who take it worthily, and the opposite for those who do not.
                <note type= "source"> Reymundus </note>
              </quote>
            </seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg3"> The Apostle [says]:
              <quote>
                let a man examine himself,
                and thus is understood what is said — carefully consider what is
                served to you, certainly such as the host of Christ.
                <note type= "source"> The Apostle </note>
              </quote>
              Hence
            </seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg4"> the verse:
              <quote>
                White, wheaten, thin, not large,
                round, without yeast, not false — the host of Christ should
                be.
                <note type= "source"> Bible verse </note>
              </quote>
            </seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg5"> Gloss: <i>White:</i> signifies chastity.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg6"> Thus you should be white, that is chaste in
              body and heart.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg7"> <i>Wheaten:</i> wheat is the sweetest of all grain,
              so you should be sweet and gentle.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg8"> <i>Thin:</i> that is moderate in food and
              drink.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg9"> <i>Not large:</i> that is humble, not proud.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg10"> <i>Round:</i> such as a round shape is moveable, so
              you should be moveable for the divine office and for doing certain
              good deeds.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg11"> <i>Without yeast:</i> yeast signifies envy and
              anger, that is you should have a sincere heart, fully devoted to
              God and your neighbours.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg12"> <i>Not false:</i> that is without greed and
              avarice.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg13">Hence Jerome [says]:
              <quote>
                I do not remember having
                read of anyone being damned who in this world led a decent life,
                that is [to have a] great will to work, and so on.
                <note type= "source"> St. Jerome </note>
              </quote>
             Following, as Ecclesiasticus says:
            </seg>
            <quote>
              <seg corresp="#seg14">
                he who worthily takes this sacrament receives thirteen blessings.
              </seg>
              <seg corresp="#seg15"> Hence the verse:
                I increase, I mingle, I
                soothe, I restrain, I terrify, I cleanse. I ignite, I enlighten,
                I double. I strengthen, I draw near, I lead. And I give life;
                upon the table so many dishes I place.
                <note type= "source"> Ecclesiasticus </note>
              </seg>
            </quote>
          <seg corresp="#seg16"> Gloss — <i>I increase:</i> namely grace in the
              present and glory in the future.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg17"> <i>I mingle:</i> that is I make [one]
              gentler.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg18"> <i>I soothe:</i> namely temptations.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg19"> <i>I restrain:</i> that is evil affection and the
              desire of the flesh.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg20"> <i>I terrify:</i> namely demons, for the demons fear
              nothing so much as the Body of Christ.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg21"> Hence Chrysostomus [says]:
              <quote>
              the Body of Christ
              repels demons and calls angels, and rightly so, because where
              their Lord is, his angels are too.
              <note type= "source"> John Chrysostomus </note>
              </quote>
              <app>
                <lem wit="#K"/>
                <rdg wit="#P">For just as cloistered monks [are accustomed] to carry the relics of the saints
                  in reliquaries, just as in a procession, so truly is it a delight to carry the magnificent
                  [relics] of the other bodies of Christ </rdg>
              </app>
            </seg>
          <seg corresp="#seg22"> <i>I cleanse:</i>>namely venial sins.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg23"> <i>I ignite:</i> namely your affection and spirit
              toward good.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg24"> <i>I enlighten:</i> namely your
              understanding.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg25"> <i>I double:</i> that is I multiply merit here and
              merit there.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg26"> <i>I strengthen:</i> namely the virtues within
              you.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg27"> <i>I draw near:</i> that is I shall be familiar in
              your soul.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg28"> <i>I lead:</i> namely out of misery and mourning to
              joy.</seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg29"> <i>I give:</i> namely eternal life.
              <app>
                <lem wit="#K"/>
                <rdg wit="#P">Which may he deign [to grant] to us, he who lives and reigns forever and ever. Amen </rdg>
              </app>
            </seg>
            <seg corresp="#seg30"> A M E N </seg>
          </p>
        </body>
      </text>

